\taxon{definition}
\title{Higher Modality}

\import{stt-macros}

\p{A higher modality is an operation on types #{\bigcirc} alongside a family of functions #{\eta_A^\circ : A \to \bigcirc A} satisfying the
following universal property:}

\p{Given a type #{A : \UU} and a family of types #{P : \bigcirc A \to \UV}, there is a function: }

##{
  \textrm{ind}_A^\circ : \Pi_{(a : A)}(P (\eta(a))) \to \Pi_{(a : \bigcirc A)}(P(a))
}

\p{
and an identity: #{\textrm{ind}(f, \eta(a)) = f(a)}

}

\p{We call a type #{\bigcirc}-modal when the map #{\eta_A : A \to \bigcirc A} is an equivalence and we also require that all identity types are #{\bigcirc}-modal.}